        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1912976911" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6366655955251775830">Bentall&apos;s book takes the reader on a compelling journey from Kraepelinian paradigm all the way to the modern(ish) society. On these pages, our conceptions, perceptions and attitudes about some of these fascinating facets of sometimes distorted human experience are examined as well as often challenged with clinician&apos;s deep experience and insight. The book skillfully balances on the famous line between sickness and health, sanity and madness without never drawing it itself. On this tour everything</span>
  <span id="freeText6366655955251775830" style="display:none">Bentall's book takes the reader on a compelling journey from Kraepelinian paradigm all the way to the modern(ish) society. On these pages, our conceptions, perceptions and attitudes about some of these fascinating facets of sometimes distorted human experience are examined as well as often challenged with clinician's deep experience and insight. The book skillfully balances on the famous line between sickness and health, sanity and madness without never drawing it itself. On this tour everything is up to question and debate, and therefore it is shame that no updated editions exist. This book exists at a focal point of seasoned expertise, and scientific argumentation is on a level that every current student should aspire to. However considering the laws that govern all science, this might also become the most fatal limitation, since on the tangled field of psychiatric research, a lot of advancement has happened in 13 years.<br />4/5</span>
  <a data-text-id="6366655955251775830" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


